What ghosts/anomalies do you encounter in the Chtulhu Mansion that is your emacs setup?
Emacs is the closest thing now existing to the vaunted &ldquo;lisp machines&rdquo; that were originally prescribed to make lisp run effectively. This seems all the more true of exwm users like myself, who are taking the proposition of &ldquo;emacs as operating system&rdquo; somewhat literally (at least, to those who don&rsquo;t consider the difference between a window manager and an operating system.